 Oooofff. A headache of unbelieved proportions. Grasping for breath, a
 small but desperate part of your wounded mind struggles to cling to
 consciousness. Something unknown, but absolutely terrible has
 happened. It's challenging to remain focused and alert, especially
 when pangs of desire for a chocolate eclair keep coming up.

 An image of a yourself, lying on the ground takes shape. Your
 belongings scattered about as if they were unimportant. Dark figures
 retreating. Too fast, the scene evaporates. Did that really happen?
 Other random feelings, images and thoughts fly by like daggers in a
 hurricane. Meanwhile an array of emotions rains down on an ocean of
 personal turmoil. Really big, turbulent waves of anger, rage and
 confusion spread across the vast surface while something sinister
 swims below.

 It wasn't always like this. Happiness did exist. Maybe whatever is
 happening is because of that dollar you stole from your best friend in
 second grade. You wonder about this as you begin to feel pulled toward
 a distant white light. The light seems to call out and provide warmth,
 safety and comfort. It could be good to move toward it. It might be
 the sane thing to do. Or it could be a trap, who knows?

 For a period of time you seem to simply float in nothingness.
 Pleasant, or at least less disturbing, dreams fill your lazy mind. You
 almost feel calm when something cold and wet brushes by your face.
 Cold fear grips you by the throat, but you kick yourself away from
 whatever is out there. The light comes blindingly back into view.
 Desparately, you push yourself toward the comforting embrace of the
 light. It envelopes you and a tingling sensation, like millions of
 tiny needles poking your skin, covers your entire body. Your mind
 explodes and is filled with the sharpest, purest and whitest
 brightness you have ever seen.

 Memory fades and later you awake standing within a beam of light. For
 the moment you feel that the nightmare of pain is over. Scratching
 your head you try to recall where you are. Slowly, a few fuzzy details
 begin to form. You realize that you have been here before. Other than
 that, everything is mostly a blank. However, for some reason you are
 wearing some kind of high-tech spacesuit and a large and familiar
 Samurai sword is strapped to your back.

 What does it mean? Where is this place? Where are you? Does it matter?

