 scale covered paws. Recognition fills your mind and you feel as if
 someone has brought the dead back to life.

 And, it smells that way too! With great revulsion, you begin holding
 you nose. You recognize one the foulest smelling creatures anywhere as
 a pitiful Hobgoblin.

 A dark corner of your mind contains a great many  details about these
 sad little creatures. The details don't all make sense, but you know
 that most of the creatures in the entire race never aspire to much,
 other than being mercenaries. They work cheap and they don't care what
 happens as long as they get paid and they don't care if you pay them
 with money, drugs, decaying scraps of meat, technology or gallons of
 putrid waste.

 As you step out of the beam, you feel a jolt of electrical energy run
 through your entire body. You gasp for breath and almost fall over.
 Staggering out of the light and onto the edge of a transport pad, you
 brace yourself for a moment at the railing. From above, a gentle wind
 caresses your body. The wind seems to carry words from some other time
 or place. The words fill your mind. You hear: "We are at war! The
 humans cannot help you."

 You rest at the railing for a moment and try to ponder these words.
 While you regain your composure the beam quickly fades and becomes
 less instense.

 A tug on your arm, rips you back to reality. The Hobgoblin, teeth
 barred in a horrible grin, is backing away and tightly grasping your
 watch.

